subSubSection.paragraph:
Integument of body and appendages satiny and opaque; surface with a finely punctate sculpture and a dense, fine pubescence. Standing pilosity sparse, usually absent on mesosomal dorsum and on petiolar node (rarely 1-2 erect setae in 
apicalis
). Body color dark brown to black. Mandibles, tarsi, and antennal funiculus often lighter in color.
